						<summary>

						<p>On the second pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Rāmanāthēśvara shrine in the Vēdāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Parāntaka I. Year 32: 938-39 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 90 sheep by Śāttaṉ Malli, a <hi rend="italic">veḷḷāṭṭi</hi> living at Kīḻai of Aḷa-nāḍu(See No. 518 above) for burning a perpetual lamp to the deity, with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily by the measure called <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
